100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 28, 1925, the League of Nations continued discussions on disarmament, reflecting ongoing concerns about global peace following the Great War. In the United States, the trial of John Scopes, accused of teaching evolution in a Tennessee school, captured national attention, igniting fierce debates over science and religion. Meanwhile, in Europe, tensions mounted as various nations grappled with economic instability, highlighting the fragility of post-war recovery.
